---
title: Vegan Apricot-Glazed Tofu & Rice Bowls with Green Beans, Sesame Seeds & Cashews
description: Savory tofu is the star of this vegan meal. Season and pan-fry it to golden perfection, then drape it in a tangy-sweet apricot-ginger glaze and serve over fragrant jasmine rice alongside tender oven-roasted green beans. Finish with a shower of nutty cashews and sesame seeds, plus a fresh flurry of scallions for the ultimate plant-based plate.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/664364b038584bf020f8c6e6-72c3c3db.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/664364b038584bf020f8c6e6-en-US.pdf
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 30 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/vegan-apricot-glazed-tofu-and-rice-bowls-664364b038584bf020f8c6e6
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 3.5 g
  carbohydrates: 109 g
  sugar: 33 g
  protein: 29 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 2680 mg
servings: 2
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

In a small #pot, combine @Jasmine Rice{3/4%cup}, 1 1/4 cups water, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, wash and dry produce.

Trim @Green Beans{6%ounce} if necessary. Peel and mince or grate @Ginger{1%thumb}. Peel and mince or grate @Garlic{2%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @Scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Open and drain @Tofu{1}; press out excess water with #paper towels. Halve crosswise, then stand tofu upright and halve vertically. Lay flat and cut into 3/4-inch cubes; season all over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Cooking Oil{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until tender and browned, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl, whisk together ginger, garlic, scallion whites, @Soy Sauce{4%tablespoon}, @Rice Wine Vinegar{5%teaspoon}, @Apricot Jam{2}, @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, 1/2 cup water, and @Sugar{1%teaspoon}.

> TIP: Don't worry if your glaze isn't smooth! It'll come together when cooked in the next step.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a large, preferably #nonstick pan{} over medium-high heat. Add tofu in a single layer and cook, undisturbed, until lightly browned on one side, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Flip tofu, then stir in apricot glaze. Cook, stirring occasionally, until glaze has thickened and tofu is evenly coated, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Fluff rice with a #fork and divide between shallow #bowls{}.

Top rice with apricot-glazed tofu and green beans in separate sections. Sprinkle everything with @Sesame Seeds{1%tablespoon}, @Cashews{1/2%ounce}, and scallion greens. Serve.